The paper deals with splitter sets, which have applications in flash memories and are related to lattice tilings and conflict avoiding codes. These topics are typically studied in the areas of information theory (cs.IT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
